      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW PASCAL (8) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage second, beaten 5.5 lengths (22.30) at Warrnambool in a Grade 5 over 390m. Can go on with it. MORE BEER PLEASE (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when sixth at Warrnambool over 390m behind Black Business (22.63) in a Grade 5 FIN. Was in the money the start prior. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from nine starts. Great chance to atone. PAW VERITY (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (22.37) at Ballarat behind Westside Wizard in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to be in this for a long way. DON'T TELL SHELL (7) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
